@page "/"
@*
    Second route so the iframe-mount flow works: the Playground loads the
    monogame template at /runtime/monogame/index.html?preview=1, and with
    <base href="./"> Blazor's NavigationManager resolves the app-relative
    path to "index.html". Without this @page Blazor's Router falls through
    to <NotFound> ("Sorry, there's nothing at this address.") and never
    renders the canvas. The standalone-from-vite-preview flow that opens
    at /runtime/monogame/ (no explicit index.html) still uses @page "/".
*@
@page "/index.html"
@inject IJSRuntime JsRuntime

<PageTitle>Fade WebRuntime.MonoGame</PageTitle>

@*
    Inline styles (not via css/app.css) so the panel works when this Razor
    component is dropped into the Playground's dockview — the Playground
    page doesn't load WebRuntime.MonoGame's app.css. canvasHolder fills
    whatever parent #mg-blazor-root resolves to; standalone wwwroot/index.html
    makes that the full viewport, Playground constrains it to a panel cell.
*@
<div id="canvasHolder" style="position: absolute; inset: 0; background: #000;">
    <canvas id="theCanvas" tabindex="0"
            style="display: block; width: 100%; height: 100%; outline: none;"></canvas>
</div>

